    "consequences" : [
    
    
    
    "In the event of repairs, seal add-on parts before assembly (painting) according to the following illustrations."
    ,
    
    
    "The surfaces to be sealed must be dry and free of grease and dirt before applying body sealant. Clean the areas with cleaning solution and a lint-free cloth."
    ,
    
    
    "The sealing material can be applied directly to add-on parts coated with KTL paint (cathodic dipbath coating)."
    ,
    
    
    "Mask or cover all adjacent areas before starting sealing work. "
    ,
    
    
    "Make sure that all residual moisture is removed completely before applying a new seal."
    ,
    
    
    "The seam seal can be painted over when a skin has formed (about 15 – 30 minutes at 20 °C, 50% relative air humidity. Higher air humidity or dampening with water accelerates the hardening process)."
    ,
    
    
    "Hardening can be checked by a nail test. Press your finger nail gently into the hardened sealing compound; if this causes no damage to the sealing compound surface, the seam seal can be painted."
    ,
    
    
    "Paint over sealing compound within 3 days."
    
    ]
    
